node.text:
Waddaaapppp! How’s everyone feline this Wonderful Wednesday? I hope all’s well! I have more free time these days thanks to CB & I’ve been occupying myself with various activities!

Like, tormenting the floof. 🤣 She’s very nice to squish. She’s pretty much resigned herself to her fate of getting squished daily by her hooman.

Of course, it’s only when she gets da treats. No treats, no squish. 
Nah I kid. She’s the best catto so she pretty much lets me have my way all the time. 🤣 
Have you been spending time with your floofs too? Of course, it doesn’t have to be a floof. 
It’s nice to take this time to just spend time with your pets or learn something! Cook that dish! Bake that cake! Learn that dance! Sing that song! Now’s the perfect time! 🤣 
Share with me what you’ve been doing during this CB! I would love to know.

Meanwhile, stay strong, stay safe & stay healthy everybody! 💪🏻💪🏻
.

The cuteeeeeeeeeeeest pic you can ever seen!!! You both are soooooo adorable, such a perfect timing the photo was taken, about her eyes look hehehe!! Actually I don't have any cats, but my close friend have. He has about 10 ones and 6 of which are family ( male, female and thier little cats). He lives next door to us, so I spend a lot of hours with him everyday as we knew each other since we were kids and our families know each other too. I enjoy these moments which I have with his cats SOOOO AWESOME TIME! For me, nowadays I start my day with some jogging in allowed hours then coming back to home for some time at the kitchen, a nother time for home exercises or yoga or even a nother activities, you know beside English language, I've studied German for 3 years at one of my education stages. I still have some German books & stories till now and I keep learning more about it. Also a few weeks ago, I began to teach myself some Spanish and A little Italian, but I hope also I can speak Japanese or Chinese, their words I feel like they draw them not writing hahaha! I have a great time to my special art room and I always have a special time for reading at night, turning off all home lights and just turn on a small candle, that's my fave reading atmosphere. Meditation is soooo good to keep the mind calm in this stressful time. You know, that deep relaxation and making your mind empty from all life problems & things JUST IMAGINE. Such like different activities to be in mood specifically these days..... Anyway, wishing you, your beautiful family and all your friends a goooooood health always! Enjoy your day dear!
